    public abstract class Dmo

      • IsEditable

        public static boolean IsEditable(@NonNull
                                 android.database.Cursor c)
        Check if a card linked to a dmo can be edited (used to display a display button). It is considered to be editable if at least one field of this dmo is editable
        Parameters:
        c - cursor should contain the following columns
        • COLUMN_VALUE_FIELD_MODE
        • COLUMN_EXPIRY_FIELD_MODE
        • COLUMN_NUMBER_FIELD_MODE
        • COLUMN_PIN_FIELD_MODE
        • COLUMN_EXTRA_LOGIN_FIELD_MODE
        • COLUMN_EXTRA_PWD_FIELD_MODE
        Returns:
        true if the card instances of this dmo can be edited, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        ValueFieldKind(android.database.Cursor), ExpiryFieldKind(android.database.Cursor), NumberFieldKind(android.database.Cursor), PinFieldKind(android.database.Cursor), ExtraLoginFieldKind(android.database.Cursor), ExtraPasswordFieldKind(android.database.Cursor)
